The new filterable-attribute projection uses an empty string as the absent-value sentinel, which collides with legitimate empty-string attribute values and returns incorrect filtered search results for that input.

Review comment:

- [P2] Avoid colliding absent attributes with empty-string values — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15b/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:15850-15855
  When a filterable attribute is a real empty string (for example `{"status":""}`) and a Rust caller filters with `SearchFilter { attributes: vec![("status", "")] }`, this `unwrap_or_default()` writes the same `''` value used for rows where the attribute is absent. The vec0 pre-KNN predicate then matches both empty-valued rows and missing-attribute rows, and the text/FTS arm mirrors the same `unwrap_or_default()` behavior in `hit_attributes_pass_filter`, so empty-string equality produces false positives instead of filtering by presence plus value.
